Title: Interesting links of the week 2025-11
Description: Here are the best and most interesting articles, blog posts, videos, podcasts, and GitHub repositories I’ve run into over the last week (March 3, 2024 - March 9, 2025). Enjoy!

Title: Performance of the Python 3.14 tail-call interpreter
Description: A deep dive into the performance of Python 3.14's tail-call interpreter: How the performance results were confounded by an LLVM regression, the surprising complexity of compiling interpreter loops, and some reflections on performance work, software engineering, and optimizing compilers.

Title: Buy European Made
Description: A directory of EU-made alternatives. From software and electronics to everyday products - all made in Europe

Title: Bispecific antibodies targeting the N-terminal and receptor binding domains potently neutralize SARS-CoV-2 variants of concern
Description: Bispecific antibodies incorporating a cross-reactive NTD-specific antibody are resilient to SARS-CoV-2 variants of concern.

Title: We’re teaming up with Qwant to build a European search index
Description: We are proud to share the next step in our journey towards tech independence: building our very own search index!

Title: What's cooking on SourceHut? Q1 2025
Description: sourcehut is a network of useful open source tools for software project maintainers and collaborators, including git repos, bug tracking, continuous integration, and mailing lists.

Title: System.Linq.Async is part of .NET 10 - LINQ for IAsyncEnumerable
Description: IAsyncEnumerable is a type that was introduced in netcoreapp3.1 times. While somewhat an enumerable (even though async in nature), it never had the capabilities as its synchronous counterpart. Until dotnet 10! Now we have some feature-parity between those two.
